    "summary": [
      "The Paris Agreement, adopted on December 12, 2015, aimed to limit global warming to 1.5°C, but global average temperatures in 2024 reached 1.45°C above the 1850–1900 baseline according to the IPCC Sixth Assessment Report.",
      " Global CO₂ emissions hit a record 37.4 gigatons in 2023, despite renewable energy expansion in countries like Germany and China, with fossil fuel consumption remaining high.",
      " Brazil's deforestation rates reached 11,568 km² in 2024, drawing criticism for President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, while India has pledged to achieve net zero by 2070, a timeline criticized by Greta Thunberg.",
      " The upcoming COP30 summit in Belém, Brazil, in November 2025, will assess international progress, and solar power capacity globally surpassed 2 terawatts in 2024, with China adding 430 gigawatts."
    ],
