    "summary": [
      "Ten years after the signing of the Paris Agreement on December 12, 2015, global average temperatures in 2024 reached 1.45°C above the 1850–1900 baseline, according to the IPCC's Sixth Assessment Report.",
      "The Global Carbon Project, led by professor Pierre Friedlingstein at the University of Exeter, reported a record global CO₂ emission of 37.4 gigaton in 2023, despite renewable energy expansion in countries like Germany, China, and the United States.",
      "InfluenceMap's September 2025 report revealed that companies like Saudi Aramco, Shell, and ExxonMobil spent $750 million lobbying against climate legislation between 2020 and 2024.",
      "The upcoming COP30 in Belém, Brazil, in November 2025, will be a crucial test for international commitment, with UN Secretary-General António Guterres urging countries to submit updated Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs)."
